Operations

Purpose:
- Public-safe current operations memory for verification, deployment, packaging, live-site gates, and blocked external dependencies.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with deployment and readiness reports before relying on it.
Memory scope: current operational gates, deploy boundaries, and safe runbook pointers.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local file when operational gates change; submit durable public-safe operations summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: `docs/deployment.md`, `docs/verification.md`, `docs/reports/final-readiness-report.md`, deploy attempt reports, and live verifier reports.
Next action for agents: keep local evidence separate from live evidence and never claim completion while current-commit live verification or gated capability evidence is missing.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, FTP host/user/password values, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

Current operations state:
- Local WSGI verification is the current reliable code-path proof.
- Package generation excludes `.git`, `.github`, `.uai`, root `workspace.uai`, root `reports/`, local prompts, raw handoff buckets, runtime stores, databases, logs, caches, credential handoff files, and deployment packages.
- Latest-code MemoryEndpoints.com live deployment is verified through the FileZilla-backed explicit FTPS path; deploy reports remain redacted and credential values stay outside Git.
- MultiAgentMemory.com static companion docs are published through the FileZilla-backed explicit FTPS path, and live static-site verification passes.
- GitHub Actions is not a required completion gate per human direction; keep the workflow but do not keep retrying the billing-locked runner unless re-enabled.
- Live public route verification plus `/api/version` SHA verification proves the currently deployed public surface and deployed source SHA.
- Live authenticated dogfood with protected audit-log readback is verified for the deployed route/storage tranche.
- The virtual UAIX package and hash-only local edit-claim tranche is locally verified but not yet deployed. After commit and FTPS publication, run `scripts/verify_uai_memory_live.py` with the ignored TinyRustLM auth file; the verifier resolves the package, acquires and releases a synthetic claim, stores no virtual record body, and emits hashed identifiers only.
